If the process receives SIGTERM (e.g., during deployment), open connections are dropped abruptly:

```js
const server = app.listen(PORT, () => { ... });
process.on('SIGTERM', () => {
  server.close(() => {
    console.log('Server shut down gracefully');
    process.exit(0);
  });
});
```

